resp_collapsed: Hi Justin - Thank you for the feedback! We work hard to make sure that our prices are competitive, so I'd love to hear more about any specific items that you felt were too expensive. Each month, we price compare items throughout the store with natural and conventional grocers in our area to make sure our prices are competitive. In addition, we offer a Food for All (FFA) Program for customers who participate in 3SquaresVT, WIC or Social Security Disability or Supplemental Income. Our FFA Program offers 10% off storewide each time participating customers shop and 15% off our Produce and Bulk departments. We also have a Co-op Basics program with hundreds of items set at everyday low prices, many which are lower than our area competitors. Of course, we do have many splurge-worthy products as well in a number of different categories, for those days when you want to treat yourself : ) - Sincerely, Allison Hope, Director of Community Engagement, ahope@citymarket.coop
name: City Market/Onion River Co-op

text: We weren't overly impressed. 20m wait some how turned into 40, and our waitress was curt with her responses and attitude. Other similar sized parties that came in much after us we're not only seated before us but also served before us. When we were served, our nachos had cold refried beans and cold chips. Guac was great tho - very fresh. The quesadilla was the saving grace, and it was pleasantly delicious. I'm not sure if it was just an 'off' night as it always appears slammed when we drive by. We were super excited to try this out, but overall my opinion is to try some of the other locations in the area before dedicating a dinner here.
